(26, 2, 'Creamy chickpea curry and sweet potato', 'A nutritious sweet potato topped with creamy chickpea curry, toasted cashews, fresh chili, and a squeeze of lime.', 'uploads/image/172710731620230119_00211.jpg', 10, 30, 'Y', '2024-09-23 16:01:56', 'Vegetarian', 'Pre-cook the sweet potatoes in the microwave to speed up the baking process.', 'uploads/thumb/1727107316172710731620230119_00211.jpg', 683, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/gas 7.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">2. Pierce your&nbsp;sweet potato with a&nbsp;fork, then cook it in the&nbsp;microwave for 5-7 minutes to allow the potato to soften.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">3.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;Add the&nbsp;sweet potato to a baking tray, drizzle with olive oil, and sprinkle with salt. Place the tray in the oven and cook for 15-20 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">4.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> While baking the potato, pre-boil water (for the coconut stock).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">5. Peel and finely chop the&nbsp;brown onion, ginger and garlic.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">6.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Heat a large non-stick frying pan with 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">7.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Once the pan is hot, add the&nbsp;chopped onion</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">with a pinch of</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">salt&nbsp;and cook for 4-6 minutes or until softened.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">8.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Once the onion has softened, add the&nbsp;chopped ginger,&nbsp;garlic, and</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">curry powder</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">and cook for 1-2 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">9. Meanwhile, chop the&nbsp;creamed coconut into pieces.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">10.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;Dissolve the&nbsp;vegetable stock mix&nbsp;and the&nbsp;chopped creamed coconut&nbsp;in 200ml of boiled water. Add more if needed.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Then, add the&nbsp;tomato paste&nbsp;and stir the ingredients together (this is the coconut stock).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">11.&nbsp;Drain and rinse the&nbsp;chickpeas.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">12. </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Add the&nbsp;coconut stock&nbsp;and&nbsp;drained chickpeas&nbsp;and cook until the sauce has thickened (roughly 5 minutes).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">13.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Once the curry has thickened, add the&nbsp;spinach&nbsp;and the juice of&nbsp;half&nbsp;a&nbsp;lime&nbsp;(this is the creamy chickpea curry).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">14. </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Once the sweet potato is cooked, add the</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">cashew nuts&nbsp;onto the baking tray and leave to cook for another few minutes until the cashews are golden and toasted.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">15. Slice your&nbsp;red chillies&nbsp;into rounds.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">16.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Cut the&nbsp;remaining lime&nbsp;into 1 wedge per person.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">17.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;Half the&nbsp;baked&nbsp;sweet potato&nbsp;and fill it with the creamy chickpea curry.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">18.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Serve with the chopped chilli, toasted cashew nuts, and a lime wedge, and enjoy!</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(27, 2, 'Greek Pork Souvlaki', 'This Greek-inspired dish features marinated pork and red peppers grilled perfectly. Served with creamy tzatziki and fresh lettuce, it\'s a quick and flavourful meal for any occasion.', 'uploads/image/172717922620230119_00315.jpg', 20, 15, 'Y', '2024-09-24 12:00:26', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Serve with flat breads to incorporate a balanced ', 'uploads/thumb/1727179226172717922620230119_00315.jpg', 602, NULL, '<p>1. Chop the pork into cubes and place it in a large bowl. Add the olive oil, oregano, lemon zest juice, paprika, and a pinch of salt. Mix well and let the pork marinate for 15 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>2. Chop the red pepper into chunks for the skewers. Dice the cucumber for the tzatziki.</p>\r\n<p>3. Combine the yoghurt, pressed garlic, and cucumber in a small bowl. Season with salt and refrigerate to keep cool.</p>\r\n<p>4. Preheat the grill to high heat. Thread the marinated pork and red pepper chunks onto a skewer, alternating between them. Place on a non-stick baking sheet and grill for 5-10 minutes on each side until cooked through and golden brown.</p>\r\n<p>5. Once the pork and peppers are cooked, serve the skewers with mixed salad leaves, sweet chilli sauce, and tzatziki.</p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein'),
(28, 2, 'Creamy chicken and sweet potato', 'This recipe features creamy, herb-infused chicken with mushrooms, onions, and garlic served alongside buttery mashed sweet potatoes. The chicken is cooked until tender and combined with a cream sauce, making it a hearty and flavourful dish.', 'uploads/image/172744359520230120_00096.jpg', 10, 30, 'Y', '2024-09-27 13:26:35', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Incorporate fresh thyme, rosemary, or parsley toward the end of cooking for a burst of fresh flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/1727443595172744359520230120_00096.jpg', 612, NULL, '<p>1. Peel and chop the sweet potato into chunks. Place the sweet potatoes in a large boiling pan, cover with water, and boil until tender (around 20 minutes).</p>\r\n<p>2. Meanwhile, chop the chicken breast into small pieces and season with salt, pepper, and dried herbs. Using a separate chopping board, chop the onion and mushrooms and mince the garlic clove. Set all ingredients aside.</p>\r\n<p>3. Once the potatoes are boiled, drain the water, then add butter, salt, and pepper to the pan. Mash the sweet potatoes until smooth.</p>\r\n<p>4. Heat the olive oil over medium heat in a frying pan. Add the chicken pieces and fry until cooked and browned. Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside.</p>\r\n<p>5. In the same pan, add 1 tbsp of olive oil. Add the chopped onions and cook for 2&ndash;3 minutes until softened.</p>\r\n<p>6. Add the minced garlic and sliced mushrooms to the pan, cooking for another 3&ndash;5 minutes until the mushrooms are tender and golden.</p>\r\n<p>7. Stir in the mixed herbs and cook for another 1&ndash;2 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>8. Pour the chicken stock into the pan with the vegetables. Bring it to a simmer and cook for about 3 minutes, allowing the stock to slightly reduce.</p>\r\n<p>9. Stir the cream and add the chicken to the pan. Allow the ingredients to simmer for another 5 minutes until the sauce thickens and is heated through. If preferred, add more salt and pepper.</p>\r\n<p>10. Serve the creamy chicken mixture next to the mashed sweet potatoes. Garnish with parsley, and enjoy!</p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(29, 1, 'Creamy mushrooms on toast', 'Toasted sourdough with creamy sautéed mushrooms, Dijon mustard, and fresh chives—quick, savoury, and flavourful.', 'uploads/image/172744518020230119_00135.jpg', 5, 10, 'Y', '2024-09-27 13:53:00', 'Vegetarian', 'Taste the mushrooms and adjust seasoning before serving to enhance flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/1727445180172744518020230119_00135.jpg', 456, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">1.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Chop the mushrooms into halves and set aside.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">2.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Toast the sourdough bread slices until golden and crispy.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">3.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Spread thin layers of the cream cheese on each slice of toast and set aside.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">4. </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Heat the olive oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat. Add the sliced mushrooms and cook, stirring frequently, for 4&ndash;5 minutes until softened and browned.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">5. </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Pour the milk, remaining cream cheese, and Dijon mustard. Stir well to coat the mushrooms evenly. Cook for 2&ndash;3 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly. Season with salt and pepper to taste.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">6. </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Spoon the creamy mushrooms onto the toasted sourdough bread. Garnish with chopped chives and serve.</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(30, 2, 'Ham mushroom and spinach frittata', 'This Ham, Spinach, and Mushroom Frittata is a flavourful, protein-packed dish. It is quick to prepare and can be enjoyed hot or cold, making it perfect for a meal-prep lunch recipe. ', 'uploads/image/172744677220230119_00091.jpg', 10, 10, 'Y', '2024-09-27 14:19:32', 'Vegetarian', 'Enhance flavour by adding fresh herbs or spices to the egg mixture.', 'uploads/thumb/1727446772172744677220230119_00091.jpg', 453, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">1. Heat your grill to its highest setting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">2. Simply slice the ham, spinach, and mushrooms into small pieces and set aside.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">3. Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil over medium-high heat in an ovenproof frying pan. Add the sliced mushrooms to the pan. Fry for 2 minutes until they soften.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">4. Stir in the chopped ham and spinach. Cook for 1 minute more, stirring occasionally, until the spinach has wilted. Season the mixture well with black pepper and a pinch of salt.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">5. Reduce the heat to medium-low. In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs and pour evenly over the vegetables and ham in the pan. Allow the frittata to cook undisturbed for 3 minutes or until the eggs are mostly set but still slightly runny in the centre.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">6. Evenly sprinkle the shredded cheese over the frittata and place the pan under the preheated grill for about 2 minutes, until the cheese is melted and the frittata is fully set.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, serif;\">7. Remove the frittata from the grill and let it cool for a minute. Cut into wedges and serve hot or cold with a handful of rocket.</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(31, 2, 'Turkey meatball quinoa salad', 'Lean turkey meatballs with courgette and herbs are baked and served with a vibrant quinoa salad—healthy, hearty, and easy to prepare!', 'uploads/image/172745281620230120_00006.jpg', 15, 35, 'Y', '2024-09-27 16:00:16', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Experiment with seasonings! Adding spices like garlic powder, onion powder, or paprika can enhance the flavour of the meatballs.', 'uploads/thumb/1727452816172745281620230120_00006.jpg', 342, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; line-height: 15pt; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;\">1. Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/180&deg;C fan/Gas 6.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; line-height: 15pt; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;\">2. Prepare the vegetables by grating the courgette and chopping the parsley into small pieces.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; line-height: 15pt; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;\">3. Put the turkey mince into a large bowl with the grated courgette, dried oregano and 1 tablespoon of the chopped parsley. Season with salt and pepper and mix until combined.&nbsp;Once fully mixed, shape the mixture into meatballs, about 1&ndash;2 inches in diameter.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; line-height: 15pt; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;\">4. Add baking paper to a baking tray and arrange the meatballs evenly spaced. Cook for 15-20 minutes and check throughout see if cooked through. Leave to stand until completely cool.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; line-height: 15pt; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;\">5. Rinse 1 cup of quinoa under cold water to remove bitterness. In a saucepan, combine the rinsed quinoa with 2 cups of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until the quinoa is fluffy and the liquid is absorbed. Set aside to cool.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 15pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; line-height: 15pt; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;\">6. In a large bowl, combine the chopped spring onion, diced red bell pepper, halved cherry tomatoes, and diced cucumber. Once the quinoa has cooled, add it to the bowl with the vegetables. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon of olive oil and 1 tablespoon of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein'),
(32, 2, 'Hoisin turkey lettuce bowls', 'Seasoned turkey mince with ginger, garlic, veggies, and hoisin sauce is served in crisp gem lettuce leaves—perfect for meal prep!', 'uploads/image/172752997220230119_00323.jpg', 10, 15, 'Y', '2024-09-28 13:26:12', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Feel free to substitute turkey with chicken, tofu, or another protein if you prefer.', 'uploads/thumb/1727529972172752997220230119_00323.jpg', 296, NULL, '<p>1. Grate the carrots, peel, and finely chop the ginger and garlic into small pieces.</p>\r\n<p>2. Cut the cucumber into slim pieces and finely chop the spring onion.</p>\r\n<p>3. Remove the leaves from the gem lettuce, wash them, and set them aside.</p>\r\n<p>4. Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.</p>\r\n<p>5. add the turkey mince and break it up once the pan is hot. Cook until it starts to brown (around 4 minutes).</p>\r\n<p>6. Once the turkey has browned, add the chopped ginger, garlic and grated carrot and cook for 2 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>7. Add the hoisin sauce, rice vinegar, and soy sauce to the pan and mix.</p>\r\n<p>8. Once all the ingredients are mixed, turn the heat low. Add the chopped cucumber and sliced spring onion to the hoisin turkey mixture, stir together, and then turn off the heat.</p>\r\n<p>9. Serve by adding the little gem lettuce leaves to a plate and load the hoisin turkey mixture on top.&nbsp;</p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, low carbohydrate'),
(33, 2, 'Summer fig and cheese salad', 'A vibrant salad with salad leaves, green beans, figs, mozzarella, shallots, and a balsamic-olive oil drizzle.', 'uploads/image/172753295720230120_00102.jpg', 10, 5, 'Y', '2024-09-28 14:15:57', 'Vegetarian', 'Use the freshest figs and mozzarella for the best flavour and texture.', 'uploads/thumb/1727532957172753295720230120_00102.jpg', 444, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">1.&nbsp;Rinse the salad leaves and set them aside.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">2.&nbsp;Trim the ends of the fine green beans and boil a pot of salted water.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">3. Add the green beans and boil for 4 minutes or until tender. Drain and rinse under cold water, then set aside.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">4.</span><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Chop the shallots into small pieces and the figs into &frac14; pieces.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">5.&nbsp;Arrange a bed of salad leaves on a long serving platter, followed by green beans, shallots, figs, and torn mozzarella.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">6. Drizzle with olive oil, balsamic dressing, salt, and pepper and serve!</span></span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(34, 3, 'Simple prawn fried rice', 'This quick, flavourful prawn-fried rice dish features green beans, peas, garlic, ginger, scrambled egg, and soy sauce—perfect for a weeknight meal.', 'uploads/image/172753813320230119_00289.jpg', 15, 15, 'Y', '2024-09-28 15:42:13', 'Pescetarian', 'Mix other proteins like chicken, tofu, or even leftover roast meat for variety.', 'uploads/thumb/1727538133172753813320230119_00289.jpg', 421, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">1.<strong> </strong>Rinse the rice under cold water until the water runs clear. Then, in a medium saucepan, combine the rinsed rice, 130 ml of water (1/2 cup) and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cover with a lid to simmer for 10-12 minutes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">2.&nbsp;While the rice is cooking, chop the green beans and spring onions, mince the garlic and ginger, and beat one egg in a bowl. Then, add all to one side.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">3. Heat the olive oil in a large wok (preferably non-stick) over medium heat. Add the minced garlic and ginger to the pan. Saut&eacute; for about 30 seconds until fragrant.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">4. Add the prawns to the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes until they turn pink and opaque. Remove them from the pan and set aside.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">5. Add the green beans to the same pan. Stir-fry for about 1 minute, then add the frozen peas and cook for another 2 minutes until cooked.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">6.<strong> </strong>Once the rice is cooked, remove it from the saucepan and add it to the wok (stirring well to combine with the vegetables).</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">7.&nbsp;Push everything to one side of the pan and pour in the beaten egg, stirring and scrambling it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">8.&nbsp;Pour in the soy sauce and white wine vinegar. Stir-fry for 2-3 minutes, ensuring everything is evenly coated.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">9.&nbsp;Return the cooked prawns to the pan, stir everything together, and cook for another minute.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">10. Add the prawn fried rice to a serving bowl and top with the chopped spring onions, sesame seeds and a sprinkle of salt if preferred.</p>', 'URL', '', '4,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate');
INSERT INTO `meals` (`id`, `meal_type_id`, `meal_title`, `meal_desc`, `meal_image`, `prep_time`, `cooking_time`, `status`, `update_on`, `food_type`, `meal_tips`, `meal_image_thumb`, `min_calorie`, `max_calorie`, `cooking_method`, `video_type`, `video_path`, `food_type_id`, `diet_type`) VALUES
(35, 3, 'Sweet chilli salmon and couscous', 'Fluffy turmeric couscous with salmon, a simple salad, and a zesty sweet chilli and lemon dressing are vibrant and nutritious.', 'uploads/image/172771889120230119_00303.jpg', 10, 20, 'Y', '2024-09-30 17:54:51', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'If you like heat, add some sliced jalapeños or a sprinkle of red pepper flakes.', 'uploads/thumb/1727718891172771889120230119_00303.jpg', 596, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. Preheat your oven to 400&deg;F (200&deg;C).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">2. Place the salmon fillets on a baking sheet. Brush each fillet with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">3. Bake for about 12-15 minutes. The salmon is ready when cooked and flakes easily with a fork.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">4.</span><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Combine the couscous (weigh 60 grams dry) and turmeric powder in a bowl. Pour boiling water over the couscous, cover, and let it sit for about 5 minutes. Fluff the couscous with a fork after it has absorbed the liquid. It should turn coloured.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">5.</span><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Chop the red onion and chilli and add to a bed of salad leaves in a serving bowl. Drizzle with lemon juice and olive oil, and then toss everything together.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">6. add the salmon and couscous in your bowl, add the sweet chilli sauce on top for flavour, and serve!</span></p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(36, 3, 'Turkey-stuffed peppers', 'These Turkey-Stuffed Peppers are a delicious and healthy dish featuring bell peppers filled with a savoury mixture of turkey mince, sautéed onions, garlic, mushrooms, and tender stem broccoli, all seasoned with cumin and topped with melted mozzarella cheese. Baked until tender, they make for a satisfying meal that’s both nutritious and flavourful—perfect for a cozy dinner!', 'uploads/image/172795440520230120_00025.jpg', 10, 25, 'Y', '2024-10-03 11:20:05', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Use lean turkey mince to reduce the fat content in this recipe.\r\n\r\n', 'uploads/thumb/1727954405172795440520230120_00025.jpg', 579, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. Preheat oven to 375&deg;F (190&deg;C).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">2. Cut the peppers in half (lengthways), then remove the seeds and core. Drizzle the peppers with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Place them upright on a baking tray and roast for 15 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">3. Chop the onion, garlic and mushrooms.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">4. Heat olive oil over medium heat in a large frying pan. Add the chopped onion and garlic, saut&eacute;ing until the onion becomes translucent, about 3-4 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">5.</span><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Stir in the mushrooms and cook until they&rsquo;re softened, about 3-4 more minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">6. Add the turkey mince to the pan, breaking it apart with a wooden spoon. Cook until it&rsquo;s browned and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">7. Stir in the cumin, stock cube, tomato puree, chopped tomatoes, and season with oregano, salt, and pepper. Allow the mixture to simmer for about 5 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">8.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Remove the peppers from the oven, fill them with the mince mix, and add the mozzarella pieces. Then, add them to the oven for 10 minutes until the cheese melts and turns golden brown. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">9. Wash the tender stem broccoli While the loaded peppers are in the oven. Bring some water to a pan and add the broccoli to simmer for 3-4 minutes. Once cooked, rinse the broccoli with a colander and set aside on a serving plate.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">10. Once the cheese has turned golden on the stuffed peppers, remove them and allow them to cool for a few minutes before serving. Enjoy!</span></p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(37, 1, 'Smoked salmon bagel', 'A toasted bagel with cream cheese, smoked salmon, avocado, lemon, and cayenne pepper—savoury and satisfying.', 'uploads/image/172805416520240607_00342.jpg', 5, 5, 'Y', '2024-10-04 15:02:45', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Add a side of salad or fruit to enhance the micronutrient content in this recipe. ', 'uploads/thumb/1728054165172805416520240607_00342.jpg', 664, NULL, '<p>1. Cut the bagel in half and toast it to your desired level of crispiness.</p>\r\n<p>2. While the bagel is toasting, cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and slice it into slim pieces.</p>\r\n<p>3. add a thin layer of cream cheese to each half once the bagel is toasted.</p>\r\n<p>4. Add the salmon to the bottom half of the bagel, then top with sliced avocado and set aside.</p>\r\n<p>5. Heat the olive oil in a non-stick frying pan on medium heat. When hot, crack in the egg, season with salt and pepper, and cook for 2-3 minutes until the egg white is set and crisp around the edges.</p>\r\n<p>6. Place the egg on the bagel base, sprinkle with cayenne and fresh lemon juice, season with salt and pepper, and serve!</p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(38, 1, 'Breakfast taco', 'These low-calorie, soft breakfast tacos feature eggs cooked in olive oil and topped with fresh chopped tomatoes and coriander. Wrapped in warm small tortillas, they offer a delightful combination of flavours and textures, making for a quick and satisfying morning meal!', 'uploads/image/172805627220230119_00136.jpg', 5, 5, 'Y', '2024-10-04 15:37:52', 'Vegetarian', 'If using corn tortillas, heat them in a dry skillet until slightly charred for extra flavour. For flour tortillas, a light toast in the skillet works well.', 'uploads/thumb/1728056272172805627220230119_00136.jpg', 331, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">1.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Chop the tomato and coriander and add into a bowl. Mix and set aside. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">2.<strong> </strong>Crack the</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> eggs into a bowl and whisk them with a pinch of salt and pepper.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">3.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a non-stick frying pan over medium heat.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">4. Once the frying pan is hot, add the eggs and immediately stir with a spatula, allowing them to cook until they are softly scrambled (2-3 minutes). Remove from heat and side aside once done.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">5.</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;In a separate frying pan, warm the two tortillas (seperate) over medium heat for 30 seconds on each side, then transfer them to a plate.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">6. Assemble the scrambled eggs onto the tortilla and top with the chopped tomatoes and coriander. Season with salt and pepper, and serve!</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(39, 1, 'Cheese and egg bagel', 'A hearty bagel with cheese, egg, and spinach—packed with protein, greens, and carbs for a satisfying breakfast.', 'uploads/image/172951163620240607_00432.jpg', 5, 10, 'Y', '2024-10-21 11:53:56', 'Vegetarian', 'Opt for a fresh bagel—everything, plain, or whole grain work well.', 'uploads/thumb/1729511636172951163620240607_00432.jpg', 511, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">1. In a medium bowl, whisk the eggs and season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">2. Heat a large frying pan over medium heat and melt the butter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">3. Add the spinach to the pan and saut&eacute; until wilted, then pour the whisked eggs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">4. Gently scramble the eggs, allowing them to form a loose omelette.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">5. When the eggs are nearly cooked, sprinkle in the cheese and let it melt.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">6. Meanwhile, toast the bagel until golden brown.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">7. To serve, spoon the cheesy egg and spinach mixture onto the bagel and add extra fresh spinach or cheese if desired.</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(40, 1, 'Cinnamon and apple yoghurt bowl', 'Cinnamon-spiced apples over creamy Greek yoghurt, topped with honey, vanilla bean, and mixed nuts—a satisfying breakfast, snack, or dessert dish.', 'uploads/image/172951368220230119_00021.jpg', 5, 10, 'Y', '2024-10-21 12:28:02', 'Vegetarian', 'For a twist, try adding a pinch of nutmeg or allspice along with the cinnamon.', 'uploads/thumb/1729513682172951368220230119_00021.jpg', 336, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">1. Cut up 1 medium red apple into slim pieces</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">2. Fill a pan with 30 ml of water and boil for 1-2 minutes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">3. Place the sliced apple in the pan and sprinkle with one teaspoon of ground cinnamon. Let the apple boil for 3-5 minutes on low heat (slow and steady wins the race).</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">4. Prepare a bed of Greek yoghurt in a small or medium-sized bowl.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">5. Finish boiling the apple once the water is absorbed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">6.&nbsp;Place the apple on top of the yoghurt.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">7. Sprinkle vanilla bean powder and honey to add sweetness</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">8.&nbsp;Add 10-20 g of preferred/mixed nuts for extra omega-3s.</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(41, 1, 'Cottage cheese bruschetta avocado', 'Toasted bread with creamy cottage cheese, cherry tomatoes, red onion, basil, avocado, and boiled eggs is a vibrant and delicious brunch option.', 'uploads/image/172951811020240607_00411.jpg', 5, 10, 'Y', '2024-10-21 13:41:50', 'Vegetarian', 'Assemble the bruschetta just before serving to maintain the crunch of the bread and freshness of the ingredients.', 'uploads/thumb/1729518110172951811020240607_00411.jpg', 489, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">1. Bring water to a gentle boil in a small saucepan.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">2. Add 2 eggs to the saucepan and poach for 6-8 minutes for a perfectly soft-boiled texture.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">3. Once cooked, transfer the eggs to an ice bath to cool, then peel and set aside.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">4. Chop the cherry tomatoes into small pieces and finely chop the red onion and the avocado into chunks. Add to a small bowl and add to one side.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">5. Season the mixture with salt and pepper, then drizzle with olive oil for added richness.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">6. Toast 1 slice of sourdough until golden and crispy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">7. Once toasted, spread the cottage cheese over the toasted sourdough. Top the cottage cheese with the vibrant bruschetta mix. Cut the poached eggs in half and place them on the toast.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">8. Finish with a sprinkle of salt and pepper and serve!</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(42, 1, 'Honey, banana and strawberry porridge', 'This strawberry, banana and honey porridge bowl features creamy oats topped with fresh sliced strawberries and bananas. Drizzled with honey, it’s a sweet and nutritious breakfast option, perfect for starting your day!', 'uploads/image/173037260720230119_00010.jpg', 3, 5, 'Y', '2024-10-31 11:03:27', 'Vegetarian', 'Adjust the amount of honey based on your preference or try adding a pinch of cinnamon for extra flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/1730372607173037260720230119_00010.jpg', 448, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. Slice 2 strawberries and chop the 30 grams of banana into small pieces.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">2. Combine 50 grams of rolled oats and 350 ml of milk in a saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, then reduce the heat and let it simmer for about 5 minutes; stir until the oats are creamy and cooked through.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">3. Once the porridge is cooked through, add the porridge into a bowl.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">4. Arrange the sliced strawberries and chopped banana on the porridge.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">5.</span><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Add 1 teaspoon of Greek yoghurt in the centre.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">6. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of chia seeds, drizzle 1 teaspoon of honey over the porridge bowl, and serve!</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(43, 1, 'Ham and mushroom frittata', 'A savoury frittata with fluffy eggs, ham, mushrooms, spinach, and cheddar, topped with rocket for a tasty breakfast.', 'uploads/image/173037501220230119_00091.jpg', 10, 15, 'Y', '2024-10-31 11:43:32', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Feel free to add other vegetables like bell peppers, onions, or zucchini for extra flavour and nutrition.', 'uploads/thumb/1730375012173037501220230119_00091.jpg', 453, NULL, '<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">1.</span><strong>&nbsp;</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Preheat your oven to 180&deg;C (350&deg;F).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">2. Chop the ham and slice the mushrooms. Wash and roughly chop the 40 grams of spinach.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">3. Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat in an oven-safe pan.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">4. Add the sliced mushrooms and cook for 3-4 minutes until they soften.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">5. Add the chopped ham and spinach to the skillet, cooking for another 2-3 minutes until the spinach wilts.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">6.</span><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Crack the 3 medium eggs into a bowl and whisk until well combined. Add a pinch of salt and pepper for seasoning.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">7. Pour the beaten eggs over the cooked ham and mushroom mixture in the skillet, evenly distributing the ingredients.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">8. Cook on the stovetop for about 2-3 minutes, gently lifting the edges with a spatula to allow uncooked eggs to flow underneath.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">9.&nbsp;Sprinkle the 15 grams of grated cheddar on top of the frittata.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">10. Transfer the pan to the preheated oven and bake for about 10 minutes until the eggs are set and the top is slightly golden.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">11.&nbsp;Once cooked, remove the frittata from the oven and let it cool for a minute.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">12. Top with 15 grams of rocket before slicing and serving and enjoy!</span></span></p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(44, 1, 'Honey and cottage cheese on toast', 'This recipe features mashed avocado spread on lightly toasted sourdough. Topped with cottage cheese and a drizzle of warm honey infused with chilli flakes.', 'uploads/image/173038974220240607_00394.jpg', 5, 3, 'Y', '2024-10-31 15:49:02', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Feel free to add other toppings like sliced radishes or cherry tomatoes for extra flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/1730389742173038974220240607_00394.jpg', 430, NULL, '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. Mash the avocado with chopped spring onion, fresh basil, and parsley in a small bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper for a flavourful blend.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">2.</span><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Lightly toast the slice of sourdough bread until golden and crispy.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">3. Spread the avocado mixture on the toasted bread.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">4. Dollop the cottage cheese over the avocado spread.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">5.</span><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Warm a drizzle of honey with a pinch of chilli flakes in the microwave for about 10 seconds, then gently drizzle it over the cottage cheese for a touch of sweetness and heat.</span></p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(45, 1, 'Oven Baked Mushroom and eggs', 'Baked mushrooms stuffed with tomatoes and eggs, seasoned with coriander and thyme, topped with fresh rocket—a hearty, flavourful breakfast or brunch.', 'uploads/image/1730391503Screenshot_2024_10_31_at_16_01_08.png', 10, 12, 'Y', '2024-10-31 16:18:23', 'Vegetarian', 'Opt for large, firm mushrooms like portobellos or large button mushrooms for better structure and flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/17303915031730391503screenshot_2024_10_31_at_16_01_08.png', 262, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">1. Begin by heating the oven to 200&deg;C (180&deg;C fan) or gas mark 6.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">2.<strong> </strong>Place the portobello mushroom, bottom side up, in a small baking dish. Gently brush each mushroom with olive oil, then season lightly with salt and pepper. Add a sprinkle of fresh coriander and thyme for extra flavour.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">3. Cover the baking dish with foil and place it in the preheated oven. Bake for 20 minutes, allowing the mushrooms to soften.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">4. After 20 minutes, remove the foil and add the tomatoes to the dish. Carefully crack an egg into each mushroom, and if desired, add an extra sprinkle of thyme, salt, and pepper.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">5. Return the dish to the oven for an additional 10-12 minutes, or until the eggs are set with runny yolks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">6. Top with fresh rocket, season with salt and pepper, and enjoy this delightful dish straight from the baking dish!</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(46, 1, 'Poached eggs with smashed avocado', 'Golden toasted sourdough with smashed avocado, poached eggs, and seasoned grilled tomatoes—a satisfying and flavorful breakfast or brunch.', 'uploads/image/173039253120230119_00116.jpg', 5, 18, 'Y', '2024-10-31 16:35:32', 'Vegetarian', 'Consider topping with chilli flakes, herbs, or feta cheese for an extra flavour boost.', 'uploads/thumb/1730392531173039253120230119_00116.jpg', 506, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">1. Preheat your grill or oven. Place the 140 g of tomatoes on a baking tray, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">2. Grill the tomatoes for 10-15 minutes, giving ample time to prepare the rest of the dish until they are tender and slightly caramelized.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">3. While the tomatoes are cooking, toast the slice of sourdough bread until golden brown. For extra flavour, spread some butter or olive oil on it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">4. Fill a saucepan with water and bring it to a gentle simmer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">5. Crack each egg into the simmering water. Poach for about 3-4 minutes for runny yolks or a bit longer for firmer yolks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">6. Use a slotted spoon to remove the eggs from the water and drain them on a paper towel.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">7. Place &frac12; avocados in a bowl and mash with a fork. Spread the smashed avocado on the toasted sourdough bread. Season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">8. Top the avocado toast with the poached eggs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">9.&nbsp;Arrange the grilled tomatoes on the side. Season with additional salt and pepper if desired, and enjoy!</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate and fat');
