(47, 1, 'Pink smoothie protein bowl', 'A creamy, fruity protein bowl with banana, berries, almond milk, and whey, topped with chia seeds and coconut for added texture and nutrition.', 'uploads/image/173390910220230119_00031.jpg', 5, 0, 'Y', '2024-12-11 09:25:02', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'If the smoothie is too thick, add a bit more almond milk or water. If it’s too thin, add more frozen fruit or a few ice cubes.', 'uploads/thumb/1733909102173390910220230119_00031.jpg', 354, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>In a blender, combine the banana, almond milk, frozen raspberries, frozen strawberries, whey protein powder, and nut butter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Blend until smooth and creamy. If needed, add a bit more almond milk to reach your desired consistency.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Pour the smoothie mixture into a bowl.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Sprinkle the desiccated coconut and chia seeds over the top with a slice of banana and strawberries.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Enjoy your delicious, protein-packed smoothie bowl!</p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(48, 1, 'Poached Eggs with Grilled Tomatoes, Broccolini & Crispy Flatbread', 'This is a light, healthy breakfast or brunch with poached eggs, tender broccolini, grilled tomatoes, and crispy flatbread for dipping.', 'uploads/image/173391312720230119_00052.jpg', 5, 15, 'Y', '2024-12-11 10:32:08', 'Vegetarian', 'Season the boiled broccolini, grilled tomatoes, and flatbread individually with salt and black pepper to build layers of flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/1733913127173391312720230119_00052.jpg', 423, NULL, '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Bring a pot of salted water to a boil. Add the broccolini and cook for 2-3 minutes until tender but still bright green. Be careful not to overcook it. Once boiled, drain the broccolini and set it aside, keeping it warm.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Preheat your grill or oven to medium-high heat.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Halve the cherry tomatoes and drizzle them with olive oil. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Grill or roast the tomatoes for 5-7 minutes, until softened and slightly charred. Remove them from the grill and set aside.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Fill a small saucepan with about 3-4 inches of water. Bring it to a gentle simmer over medium heat.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Crack each egg into a small bowl or cup. Gently slide the eggs into the simmering water.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Poach the eggs for about 3-4 minutes for a soft, runny yolk, or longer if you prefer a firmer yolk.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Once done, carefully remove the eggs with a slotted spoon and set them on a paper towel to drain.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Toast the flatbread slices until golden and crispy, about 2-3 minutes in a toaster, grill, or on a pan.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">On a plate, arrange the boiled broccolini and grilled cherry<strong> </strong>tomatoes, add the flatbread and place the poached egg on top.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Season with extra salt and pepper if needed, and enjoy!</span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, low carbohydrate'),
(49, 1, 'Soft boiled egg with asparagus and grilled tomatoes', 'A light, flavourful breakfast or brunch with a soft-boiled egg, grilled asparagus, and charred cherry tomatoes.', 'uploads/image/173391365020230119_00040.jpg', 5, 10, 'Y', '2024-12-11 10:40:50', 'Vegetarian', 'This recipe is perfect for a light breakfast or snack that contains fibre and protein to keep you fuller for longer!', 'uploads/thumb/1733913650173391365020230119_00040.jpg', 257, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Fill a small boiling pan with water and bring it to a boil.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Gently place the egg in the boiling water and cook for 4-5 minutes for a soft-boiled egg with a runny yolk (if you prefer a firmer yolk, cook for 6-7 minutes).</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>While the egg is boiling, preheat your grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Once the egg is boiled, remove it from the water and place it in a bowl of cold water to stop the cooking. Once cooled, carefully peel the egg and set it aside.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Trim the woody ends of the asparagus and coat them lightly with 5ml of olive oil&mdash;season with a pinch of sea salt and black pepper. Halve the cherry tomatoes and drizzle them with the remaining<strong> </strong>5ml of olive oil&mdash;season with a pinch of<strong> </strong>sea salt<strong> </strong>and black pepper.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">6.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Place the asparagus and halved cherry tomatoes on the grill (or in the pan). Grill for about 4-5 minutes, turning the asparagus pieces occasionally, and letting the tomatoes cook for 2-3 minutes. The asparagus should be tender and lightly charred, while the tomatoes should soften and get a slight char.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">7.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Add the egg to an egg cup on a plate and gently crack the top with a spoon or knife to reveal the runny yolk. Add the asparagus and the tomatoes to one side and serve!</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, low carbohydrate'),
(50, 1, 'Raspberry bircher with mixed nuts and seeds', 'A nutritious and delicious breakfast or snack with creamy yoghurt, oats, crunchy nuts, sweet apple, and vibrant raspberry sauce.', 'uploads/image/173391409420230119_00006.jpg', 5, 20, 'Y', '2024-12-11 10:48:14', 'Vegetarian', 'Allow the oats to soak for 15 minutes to soften and absorb the flavours, but you can let it soak longer if you prefer a softer texture.', 'uploads/thumb/1733914094173391409420230119_00006.jpg', 562, NULL, '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Combine the porridge oats, chopped nuts, sunflower seeds, dried fruits (optional), sliced apple, apple juice, and Greek-style yoghurt in a large bowl.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Stir everything together to combine. Let the mixture soak for about 15 minutes to allow the oats to soften slightly and absorb some of the liquids.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">In a blender, combine the honey and raspberries (reserving a few raspberries for serving). &nbsp;Blend until smooth. Taste and adjust sweetness with extra honey if needed.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">Once the oats have softened, drizzle the raspberry sauce over the top, garnish with the reserved fresh raspberries for a finishing touch, and enjoy!</li>\r\n</ol>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High carbohydrate'),
(51, 1, 'Mixed berry protein smoothie', 'A mixed berry protein smoothie combines nutrient-rich berries with protein, boosting antioxidants, fibre, and protein to support muscle recovery, immune health, and overall wellness.', 'uploads/image/173460777420230120_00117.jpg', 5, 0, 'Y', '2024-12-19 11:29:34', 'No Dietary Restriction', 'Use fresh or frozen berries to enhance antioxidants, vitamins and fibre. ', 'uploads/thumb/1734607774173460777420230120_00117.jpg', 254, NULL, '<p style=\"margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', sans-serif;\">1. Add the banana, protein powder, almond milk, oats, frozen berries, chia seeds and honey into a blender (leave a sprinkle of chia seeds for a topping!).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', sans-serif;\">2. Blend the ingredients until a smoothie texture is formed.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', sans-serif;\">3. Serve into a cup or glass.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-right: 0cm; margin-left: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\', sans-serif;\">4. Top with a sprinkle of chia seeds and a mint leaf.</span></p>', 'URL', '', '5,', 'High protein, moderate carbohydrate'),
(52, 4, 'Soft boiled egg', 'A soft-boiled egg is a nutrient-packed snack, offering high-quality protein, healthy fats, and essential vitamins like B12, D, and choline. With its creamy yolk, it\'s a quick, satisfying option that supports muscle health. ', 'uploads/image/173460898420230120_00072.jpg', 2, 8, 'Y', '2024-12-19 11:49:44', 'Vegetarian', 'Sprinkle with salt and pepper, and chilli flakes for extra flavour.', 'uploads/thumb/1734608984173460898420230120_00072.jpg', 144, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 54pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Boil water and fill a small saucepan with enough water to cover the eggs by about an inch. Bring it to a boil over medium-high heat.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 54pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Using a spoon to avoid cracking once the water is boiling, gently lower the eggs into the water.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 54pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Reduce the heat to a gentle simmer and cook the eggs for 6-7 minutes for a soft, runny yolk. For slightly firmer yolks, cook for 8 minutes.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 54pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Using a spoon, transfer the eggs to a bowl of ice water or run under cold water for a few minutes to stop the cooking process.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 54pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Gently tap the eggs to crack the shells, then peel. Serve with a pinch of salt, pepper, and chilli flakes.</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High protein, low carbohydrate'),
(53, 1, 'Vanilla and Raspberry Overnight Oats', 'This overnight oat recipe is a quick, creamy breakfast that combines oats, vanilla yoghurt, honey, milk, and raspberries. Refrigerate overnight for a ready-to-eat, flavourful and sweet meal the following day. \r\n\r\n', 'uploads/image/173546634820240607_00034.jpg', 5, 0, 'Y', '2024-12-29 09:59:09', 'Vegetarian', ' Enjoy cold the following morning, or store for up to 2 days in the fridge.', 'uploads/thumb/1735466348173546634820240607_00034.jpg', 304, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">In a bowl, combine 45 g of rolled oats.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Add 2 tablespoons of vanilla yoghurt to the oats.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">If preferred, drizzle in 5 ml of honey and mix to combine for extra sweetness.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Pour 120 ml of milk into the mixture and stir until well combined.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Gently fold in 50 g of frozen raspberries.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">6.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Transfer the mixture into a jar or airtight container.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">7.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Top with an additional layer of vanilla yoghurt and a handful of fresh raspberries.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">8.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow the oats to soak and the flavours to meld.</span></p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High carbohydrate'),
(55, 1, 'Strawberry and banana overnight oats', 'Strawberry and Banana Overnight Oats are a quick, creamy breakfast made by combining oats, chia seeds, yogurt, and fresh fruit. Just mix, refrigerate overnight, and enjoy the next morning.', 'uploads/image/173546803920240607_00213.jpg', 5, 0, 'Y', '2024-12-29 10:27:19', 'Vegetarian', 'Enjoy cold the following morning, or store for up to 2 days in the fridge.', 'uploads/thumb/1735468039173546803920240607_00213.jpg', 419, NULL, '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>In a bowl, combine the oats, walnuts, chia seeds, yoghurt, vanilla extract, blueberries, banana, milk, and syrup. Stir well to ensure all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Transfer the mixture into a glass container or airtight jar.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Top with additional blueberries and banana slices for garnish.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt; line-height: 15.5467px; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; text-indent: -18pt;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow the ingredients to soak and flavours to develop.</p>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'High carbohydrate'),
(56, 1, 'Veggie Sausage & Poached Egg Breakfast Toast', 'A hearty, delicious breakfast of veggie sausage, poached egg, sautéed mushrooms, and wilted spinach on crispy pesto sourdough topped with fresh rocket is a satisfying and nutritious start to your day.', 'uploads/image/173600757720230119_00102.jpg', 5, 15, 'Y', '2025-01-04 16:19:37', 'Vegetarian', 'For a different flavour profile, swap veggie sausages for plant-based breakfast patties, tempeh, or even grilled portobello mushrooms.', 'uploads/thumb/1736007577173600757720230119_00102.jpg', 452, NULL, '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\">Bring a large pan of water to a gentle simmer (not a rolling boil). Crack the egg into a small ramekin or cup. Once the water is simmering, gently slide the egg into the water. Let it cook for 2-3 minutes until the whites are set, but the yolk is still runny. Carefully remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Heat a non-stick frying pan over medium heat with olive oil. Add the veggie sausage and cook for 5-7 minutes, turning occasionally, until it is golden and slightly crisp outside. Once cooked, remove it from the pan and set aside.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">In the same pan, add another teaspoon of olive oil. Add the sliced mushrooms and saut&eacute; for 5-7 minutes until caramelised.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Add the spinach to the pan at the last minute and cook until just wilted.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">While the mushrooms and spinach are cooking, toast your sourdough slices to your desired level of crispiness.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Spread a thin layer of pesto on top of the toasted bread. Layer the saut&eacute;ed mushrooms, spinach, and egg on top. Add the sausage and rocket next to the toast.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Sprinkle salt and pepper and serve!</span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'URL', '', '9,', 'Moderate protein, moderate carbohydrate');
