our torso upright and your elbows in the front rack position throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return and Repeat: </strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Push through the front leg to return to standing, and repeat for the desired number of reps.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Dumbbells', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730486034Screenshot_56.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/kL0uJV199i0', 'Y', '2024-11-01 18:33:54', 'uploads/thumb/17304860341730486034screenshot_56.png', 3, 'Full Body', NULL, NULL, 2, 2),
(62, 7, 'Frog stretch', 'Your hands can be placed wider to increase the range of motion.', '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Setup:</strong> Kneel in front of a bench/box, placing your hands wider than shoulder-width on the edge.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Position:</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Keep your elbows straight, engage your core, and lower your hips back while spreading your knees outward.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Stretch:</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Drop your head and chest toward the floor, feeling the stretch in your hips, groin, and lower back.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Hold:</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Maintain the position for 20-30 seconds, breathing deeply.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Release:</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> Slowly return to the starting position by </span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">bringing your hips forward and relaxing</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 1, 2, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730487338Screenshot_57.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/jCLXlxdtI6M', 'Y', '2024-11-01 18:55:38', 'uploads/thumb/17304873381730487338screenshot_57.png', 2, 'Full Body', NULL, NULL, 2, 2),
(63, 7, 'Sumo deadlift (frog)', 'Choose a foot width that feels comfortable for you.', '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Set Up Your Feet</strong>: Position your feet in a squat stance or slightly wider, with toes pointed outward.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Grip the Bar</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Grip the bar with your hands in a standard deadlift position, just inside your knees.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Engage Your Core</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep your back flat and chest up, ensuring your spine stays neutral throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Lift the Bar</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Perform the deadlift by simultaneously driving through your heels and</span> <span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">extending your hips and knees. Keep your arms loose and the bar close to your body.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Track the Knees</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Ensure your knees track in line with your toes throughout the movement, avoiding inward collapse.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Maintain Balance</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As you stand tall, distribute your weight evenly through your feet, with pressure on your heels and midfoot.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Barbell', 5, 5, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730542866Screenshot_58.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/sfxgHXqPalw', 'Y', '2024-11-02 10:21:06', 'uploads/thumb/17305428661730542866screenshot_58.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 2, 1),
(64, 7, 'Baby stretch from flat back', 'Can be performed for repetitions or held in position.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lie on your back with your spine flat against the floor and your legs extended straight.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grip Your Toes</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: in