ower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Dumbbells', 12, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730663330Screenshot_61.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/u1rDFA0jUlc', 'Y', '2024-11-03 19:48:50', 'uploads/thumb/17306633301730663330screenshot_61.png', 2, 'Shoulders', NULL, NULL, 1, 5),
(67, 7, 'Devil press', 'Execute the snatch quickly. This exercise can also be performed with a single dumbbell and alternating hands.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start with the Dumbbells</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin standing with a dumbbell in each hand, positioned in front of you.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Perform a Burpee</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Holding the dumbbells in each hand, drop into a burpee by squatting down, placing your hands on the floor, and kicking your feet back into a plank position. Make sure your chest touches the floor.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return to the Dumbbells</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Push your chest off the floor, jump your feet back, explosively bring the dumbbells into an overhead position, and lock the elbows. Repeat the movement.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730663711Screenshot_62.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/3OXiP81XFl4', 'Y', '2024-11-03 19:55:11', 'uploads/thumb/17306637111730663711screenshot_62.png', 3, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 4),
(68, 7, 'Chest press', 'Can also be performed on the floor as a floor press.', '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Set Up</strong>: Lie flat on a bench with your head and back firmly pressed against the surface, holding a dumbbell in each hand at chest level.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Press the Dumbbells Up</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Press the dumbbells upwards, locking your arms in a fully extended position directly over your shoulders.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Keep Forearms Vertical</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Ensure your forearms remain vertical throughout the movement, avoiding any outward or inward angle.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Lower the Dumbbells</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly lower the dumbbells back to chest level, maintaining control and keeping the forearms vertical.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Dumbbells', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730664114Screenshot_63.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/cZG2vGsSUfY', 'Y', '2024-11-03 20:01:54', 'uploads/thumb/17306641141730664114screenshot_63.png', 2, 'Chest', NULL, NULL, 1, 4),
(69, 7, 'Bent over reverse fly', 'This movement can be performed lying face down on a bench for added support.', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Hinge at the Hips</strong>: Bend at the hips, keeping your back flat until your torso is just above parallel to the floor.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Position Your Arms</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: With your arms straight and elbows pointing slightly outward, hold a dumbbell in each hand.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Raise the Dumbbells</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly raise both dumbbells to the sides, bringing them as high as possible under control while keeping your arms straight.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Maintain Spine Position</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep your back neutral and avoid rounding or arching throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Dumbbells', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730664432Screenshot_64.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/qQg0IR92Oao', 'Y', '2024-11-03 20:07:12', 'uploads/thumb/17306644321730664432screenshot_64.png', 3, 'Back', NULL, NULL, 1, 3),
(70, 7, 'Downward dog', 'This movement can be performed for repetitions or held in each position', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start in Plank Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Lower the Hips</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Drop your hips toward the floor while keeping your arms straight and locked. Relax in this position to feel a gentle stretch.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Lift the Hips</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Press through your hands and lift your hips as high as possible, aiming to create an \"A-frame\" shape with your body.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Push Through the Arms</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As you raise your hips, push your head through your arms, elongating your spine and deepening the stretch.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hold and Breathe</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Relax into the position and breathe deeply, feeling the stretch in your hamstrings, calves, and shoulders.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 1, 2, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730664699Screenshot_65.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/V5-LYE3eU6Y', 'Y', '2024-11-03 20:11:39', 'uploads/thumb/17306646991730664699screenshot_65.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 3),
(71, 7, 'Conventional deadlift', 'Proper positioning is crucial—don’t compromise it for heavier weight on the bar.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Foot Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Position your heels directly under your hip joints, with your toes turned slightly outward.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grip the Bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Reach down and grip the bar just outside shoulder width, keeping your arms relaxed.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set the Back</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lift your chest to create a neutral spine, ensuring your back is flat and not rounded.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hips and Shoulders Alignment</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Set your hips slightly above your knees and your shoulders directly over the bar, keeping the bar close to your shins.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Weight Distribution</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Ensure your weight is evenly distributed through your feet, with pressure through the heels and midfoot.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Brace the Shoulders</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Engage your shoulders by pulling them back and down while keeping your arms loose and straight.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Lift the Bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin the lift by extending your hips and knees, maintaining a straight back. Keep the bar directly over your feet throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Finish the Lift</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand tall, locking your hips and knees </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">fully</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> without leaning back or overextending.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Barbell', 5, 5, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730665176Screenshot_66.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/R7OZV8XVLjA', 'Y', '2024-11-03 20:19:36', 'uploads/thumb/17306651761730665176screenshot_66.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 3);
