(72, 7, 'Dead hang', 'A great foundation for building the strength needed for a pull-up', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grip the Bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Reach up and grab the pull-up bar with your hands just outside shoulder width, ensuring your palms face forward or towards you (depending on your grip style).</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Engage Your Shoulders</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Engage your shoulders by pulling them back and down before </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">fully</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> hanging. Avoid letting them rise toward your ears.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hang</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Let your body </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">fully</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> hang from the bar, keeping your arms extended and elbows slightly bent.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Relax Your Upper Body</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Allow your back, midriff, and spine to relax into the stretch. Focus on decompressing your spine, allowing gravity </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">to naturally lengthen it</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Maintain the Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Hold the hang while breathing </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">deeply</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> and maintaining a relaxed posture. You should feel a gentle stretch through your shoulders, upper back, and spine.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: When ready, pull yourself up to the bar or gently lower your feet to the ground to exit the hang.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 1, 2, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730665735Screenshot_68.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/Oa3zSJkBv9M', 'Y', '2024-11-03 20:28:56', 'uploads/thumb/17306657351730665735screenshot_68.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 2),
(73, 7, 'Coach stretch', 'This can be performed with glide reps or held at the stretch position.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Position the back foot</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Place one foot onto the edge of a bench or elevated surface with your knee resting on the floor.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set up the front leg</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Step your other leg forward comfortably, ensuring your knee is at a 90-degree angle.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Engage your core</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Suck your stomach in and engage your core to stabilize your torso.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Maintain an upright torso</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep your chest lifted and your torso upright to avoid excessive arching in your lower back.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Tense your glutes</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Squeeze your glutes to help engage the hips and prevent overextension in the lower back.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Push hips forward</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Gently drive your hips forward, aiming to feel a stretch in the hip flexors of the leg that\'s extended behind you.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hold the stretch</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Maintain the stretch while focusing on breathing deeply and holding the position for the desired amount of time.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 1, 2, NULL, 'uploads/image/1730666086Screenshot_69.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/8jmVnpAkR8k', 'Y', '2024-11-03 20:34:46', 'uploads/thumb/17306660861730666086screenshot_69.png', 2, 'Quadriceps', NULL, NULL, 1, 2),
(74, 7, 'Copenhagen side hold', 'Ensure both sides are held for the same duration to maintain balanced strength and endurance.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start in a side plank position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin by lying on your side with your forearm on the floor directly beneath your shoulder, ensuring your body is straight.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Stack your body</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: init