(77, 10, 'Bunny hop', 'Maintain a continuous, cyclical motion, flowing seamlessly from one jump to the next.', '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Start in a squat position</strong>: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and your body in a low squat position.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Prepare to jump</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Engage your core and drive through your legs to prepare for the jump. Keep your chest up and your eyes forward.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Jump forward</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Perform a </span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">small</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">, explosive jump forward, using both feet simultaneously. Focus on a quick, fluid movement.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Land softly</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Land gently in a squat position, keeping your knees slightly bent to absorb the impact. Immediately prepare for the next jump.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Continue jumping</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep the movement smooth and continuous, hopping from one jump directly into the next without pausing.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 4, 15, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734006850Screenshot_74.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/ie3FQkt05BU', 'Y', '2024-12-12 12:34:10', 'uploads/thumb/17340068501734006850screenshot_74.png', 2, 'Full Body', NULL, NULL, 2, 1),
(78, 10, 'Broad jump', 'The jump distance should be limited to a range where you can maintain a stable and controlled landing.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start with feet hip-width apart</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and your arms relaxed at your sides.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Prepare to jump</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Bend your knees and swing your arms back to load your hips, preparing for an explosive jump.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Jump forward</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Explosively jump forward, driving through your hips and swinging your arms forward to generate momentum. Focus on jumping as far horizontally as possible.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Land softly</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Land in a controlled squat position, with your knees bent and hips low to absorb the impact. Ensure your feet land flat on the ground, with your weight evenly distributed.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Stand to finish</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: From the squat position, stand up tall and reset your stance before performing the next rep.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 4, 6, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734007125Screenshot_77.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/3xDxl-z2wsU', 'Y', '2024-12-12 12:38:45', 'uploads/thumb/17340071251734007125screenshot_77.png', 3, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(79, 11, 'Box jump', 'This exercise can be made more challenging by increasing both the height of the box and the elevation of your hips in the landing position.', '<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Stand safely</span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">: Position yourself about an arm\'s length away from the box, with your feet shoulder-width apart. Ensure you\'re at a safe distance to jump onto the box comfortably.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></strong><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Prepare to jump</span></span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">: Slightly bend your knees and swing your arms back, loading your hips in preparation for the jump. Keep your chest up and core engaged.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></strong><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Jump explosively</span></span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">: Use your hips and arms to drive upward in a two-footed jump. Swing your arms forward as you jump, aiming for a smooth, controlled landing.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></strong><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Land in a squat position</span></span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">: Land softly on the box with both feet, absorbing the impact by bending your knees and controlling the landing into a squat. Keep your knees aligned with your toes.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></strong><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Stand up fully</span></span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">: Push through your heels to stand tall on the box, ensuring you\'re fully balanced and stable before finishing the rep.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; text-indent: -18pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">6.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></strong><strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">Step down</span></span></strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: #0e101a;\">: Carefully step down from the box one foot at a time, maintaining control and ensuring your knees don\'t buckle as you land.</span></span></p>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 8, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734218699Screenshot_78.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/eNP9pbIbFKw', 'Y', '2024-12-14 23:24:59', 'uploads/thumb/17342186991734218699screenshot_78.png', 3, 'Full Body', NULL, NULL, 1, 1);
INSERT INTO `workout` (`id`, `routine_id`, `workout_title`, `workout_tipe`, `workout_desc`, `workout_type`, `equipments`, `rep`, `sets`, `worktime`, `image`, `video_type`, `url_type`, `video_path`, `status`, `update_on`, `workout_image_thumb`, `workout_level_id`, `musclegroup`, `min_calorie`, `max_calorie`, `week_no`, `day_no`) VALUES
(80, 6, 'Bird Dog', 'Arching your back or twisting your hips is common when lifting the arm or leg higher. Focus on extending the limb fully rather than trying to increase height.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start in a neutral all-fours position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin on your hands and knees with your wrists under your shoulders and knees under your hips. Keep your back flat and your core engaged.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Extend opposing arm and leg</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly raise your right arm straight out in front of you while simultaneously extending your left leg straight behind you, keeping your hips level and your back neutral.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Maintain position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Hold the extended position momentarily, ensuring your back and hips stay stable and don\'t rotate or sag.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return to start</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lower your arm and leg back to the starting position with control, then repeat on the opposite side.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 5, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734219018Screenshot_79.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/vr-L4lb4feo', 'Y', '2024-12-14 23:30:18', 'uploads/thumb/17342190181734219018screenshot_79.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(81, 5, 'Bent over Row', 'If your back position is compromised, regressing to an inverted row is a good alternative.', '<p>deadlift the bar to a standing position, then hinge at the hip with soft bend at the knee, until the torso is just above horizontal to the floor, row the bar into low chest maintaining posistion&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Barbell', 6, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734440052Screenshot_81.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/kqIxb0mthCE', 'Y', '2024-12-17 12:54:12', 'uploads/thumb/17344400521734440052screenshot_81.png', 3, 'Posterial Chain', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(83, 6, 'Barbell reverse and forward lunge', 'This exercise can be modified by using dumbbells instead of a barbell.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set up the bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Step out of the rack with the bar in the back rack position, resting on your traps. Ensure your feet are shoulder-width apart, and grip the bar with your hands just outside shoulder-width.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Engage your core</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand tall with your chest lifted and core engaged, and maintain an upright torso throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Step back</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Take a controlled stride backwards with one leg, lowering your hips as you drop the back knee toward the floor.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Control the descent</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Aim for a 90-degree bend in your front knee and a close-to-90-degree bend in your back knee. Your back knee should gently touch the floor without slamming.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Push through the front foot</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Press through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position, bringing your back leg forward.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Repeat</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions, keeping your torso upright and maintaining control throughout.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Barbell', 6, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734440691Screenshot_83.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/dbewk9dOsoE', 'Y', '2024-12-17 13:04:51', 'uploads/thumb/17344406911734440691screenshot_83.png', 2, 'Full Body', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(84, 7, 'Barbell bicep curl', 'Avoid swinging your back or using momentum to lift the bar—control the motion and focus on the bicep contraction throughout.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Stand tall</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core engaged for stability.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grip the bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Hold the barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), positioning your hands shoulder-width apart.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Position your elbows</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep the elbows close to your sides, ensuring they stay stationary throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Curl the bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly curl the barbell upwards, focusing on contracting your biceps. Keep your elbows fixed in place, avoiding any movement at the shoulder.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Reach the top</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Curl the bar as high as possible, aiming to bring it close to your chest without moving your back or elbows.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Lower with control</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms but maintaining control throughout the descent.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Repeat</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Continue to perform the movement with smooth, controlled reps, focusing on form and muscle engagement.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Barbell', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734440918Screenshot_84.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/FYQ1c9n4GA8', 'Y', '2024-12-17 13:08:38', 'uploads/thumb/17344409181734440918screenshot_84.png', 2, 'Biceps', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(85, 6, 'Backsquat', 'Heel wedges can be used to help improve squat depth.', '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set the squat rack height</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Adjust the squat rack so the J-hooks are at mid-chest height, ensuring easy access to the bar.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Position the bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Step under it and position it just below the base of your neck, resting on your trap muscles. Make sure the bar is stable and securely in place.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grip the bar</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Bring your hands in as close as is comfortable, ensuring a firm grip on the bar with your elbows slightly pointed down and back.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Lift the bar off the rack</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand tall and lift the bar off the rack using your legs (not your back), then take two steps back to clear the rack.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set your stance</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Position your feet slightly wider than hip-width apart, with your toes pointing slightly outward, for better stability and hip mobility.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Squat down</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep your back neutral (avoid rounding or excessive arching), lower your body into a squat, push your hips back, and bend your knees. Squat as deep as possible while maintaining a neutral spine.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Track the knees</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Ensure your knees track over your toes and don\'t cave in. Keep your weight distributed evenly through your midfoot, with the heels flat.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Stand back up</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Push through your heels and midfoot to drive your body to a standing position, keeping your back neutral and core engaged.</span></p>', '', 'Barbell', 5, 5, NULL, 'uploads/image/1734441312Screenshot_85.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/I1cULLssftE', 'Y', '2024-12-17 13:15:12', 'uploads/thumb/17344413121734441312screenshot_85.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(86, 9, 'Baby stretch from squat', 'For the flat back variation, ensure your spine remains neutral and avoid rounding as you lift your hips.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start in a deep squat</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin in a squat position with your feet shoulder-width apart, and your knees pushed outward.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grab your toes</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Reach down and grab your toes with both hands, keeping your arms on the inside of your knees.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Pull hips down</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Gently pull your hips toward the floor, deepening the squat as much as your mobility allows.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Raise your hips</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: From the deep squat, lift your hips as high as possible, aiming to straighten your legs while keeping your back as flat as possible.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return to squat</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Repeat your hips into the deep squat position.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 10, 3, NULL, 'uploads/image/1735931230Screenshot_86.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/yoGz39n_7Zo', 'Y', '2025-01-03 19:07:11', 'uploads/thumb/17359312301735931230screenshot_86.png', 2, 'Full Body', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(87, 7, 'Bench Press', 'Ensure your grip on the bar is secure by wrapping your thumb around the bar to meet your fingers in a conventional grip. For added safety, it’s also recommended to use a spotter.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set up on the bench</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lie flat on your back with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Ensure your back and hips remain in contact with the bench throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\