(93, 7, 'Plate frontal raise', 'This exercise can also be performed seated and with a dumbbell if needed.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start standing</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the plate with both hands in front of your chest.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Engage your posture</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Ensure your shoulders are back and your back is straight. Brace your core to stabilise your body.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Raise the plate</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: With your arms fully extended and locked, press the plate overhead in a controlled manner, maintaining a strong, upright posture.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Finish in the lockout</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Your arms should be fully extended at the top, with the plate directly overhead. Keep your shoulders down and engaged throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Lower with control</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Reverse the motion, returning the plate to the starting position, maintaining your posture and control.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Barbell', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736194119Screenshot_94.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/xkQyZIgo_1k', 'Y', '2025-01-06 20:08:39', 'uploads/thumb/17361941191736194119screenshot_94.png', 2, 'Shoulders', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(94, 10, 'Plate Ground to Overhead', 'If a plate is unavailable, this exercise can also be performed with a dumbbell in the same movement pattern, focusing on driving through the legs for power.', '<p><span style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. With your back flat and using your legs, lower the edge of the plate to the floor. In one smooth motion, drive through your legs and lift the plate overhead, locking your arms at the top.</span></p>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 15, 3, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736277774Screenshot_95.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/L56FP9xb5Co', 'Y', '2025-01-07 19:22:54', 'uploads/thumb/17362777741736277774screenshot_95.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(95, 7, 'Plate Overhead Sit-up', 'If the exercise is too difficult, it can be done without a plate, and you can anchor your feet for added stability.', '<p><span style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">1. Hold the weight plate overhead with your arms fully extended and locked. Perform a sit-up while keeping the plate overhead throughout the movement.</span></p>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736278042Screenshot_96.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/JUnbli7cGi4', 'Y', '2025-01-07 19:27:22', 'uploads/thumb/17362780421736278042screenshot_96.png', 2, 'Abdominals', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(96, 10, 'Russian Twist', 'To make it easier, you can anchor your feet, and use a kettlebell or dumbbell instead of a plate.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Sit up tall</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin in a seated position with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor (you can also lift your feet off the ground for an added challenge). Hold the plate by its edges with both hands, extending your arms in front of your chest.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Engage your core</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lean back slightly to activate your core muscles. Keep your back straight, not rounded, and engage your abs throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Rotate to one side</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Twist your torso to one side, bringing the plate toward the floor next to your hip, without letting it touch your body. Keep your arms extended, and avoid letting the plate rest on your torso.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Control the movement</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly return to the centre, maintaining tension in your core, and then rotate to the other side, bringing the plate toward the opposite floor.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Maintain a steady rhythm</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Continue alternating sides in a controlled manner, keeping your movements fluid and engaging your obliques and core.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 12, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736363370Screenshot_97.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/Q85D8zE5oAk', 'Y', '2025-01-08 19:09:30', 'uploads/thumb/17363633701736363370screenshot_97.png', 2, 'Abdominals', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(97, 5, 'Nordic Hamstring curl', 'Begin by kneeling with your feet securely anchored under a bar or another stable object. Keep your body in a straight line from your knees to your shoulders.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Position your body</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Start </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">by</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> kneeling with your partner, holding your ankles securely. Keep your body in a straight line from your knees to your shoulders.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Engage your core</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Tighten your core and glutes to maintain stability and prevent any sagging in the lower back during the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Control the descent</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly hinge at the knees, keeping your torso upright, and lower yourself towards the ground. Aim to control the descent as much as possible, resisting gravity.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Go as low as possible</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lower yourself as far as your strength and control allow. The key is to go slow and stay engaged throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Cushion the descent</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As you reach your limit, use your arms to help cushion your fall, pressing them against the floor to slow and control the landing.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return to the start</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Push through your hamstrings, glutes, and core to reverse the motion and return to the starting position, maintaining a straight line from your knees to your shoulders.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Bodyweight, Bodyweight', 5, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736363973Screenshot_98.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/nPctQTUh7J8', 'Y', '2025-01-08 19:19:33', 'uploads/thumb/17363639731736363973screenshot_98.png', 4, 'Hamstrings', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(98, 10, 'Kettlebell clean', 'This movement can be simplified with a dumbbell to reduce wrist rotation.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Starting position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin standing or with the kettlebell on the floor between your feet.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set your back</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Keep your chest lifted and back straight, engaging your core throughout the movement.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Grip and pull</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: With a firm grip on the kettlebell, initiate the movement by driving through your hips and pulling the kettlebell close to your body. The motion should be quick and explosive.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Keep it close</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As you pull, the kettlebell should stay close to your body, almost brushing your inner thigh or hip. </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">This</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"> minimises swing and maximises control.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Rack position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: In one swift motion, bring the kettlebell up and rotate the wrist to catch the bell in the \"front rack\" position. Your elbow should be tucked in, and the kettlebell should rest against your forearm and upper arm.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Finish with a straight wrist</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Ensure your wrist is straight and stable and the kettlebell securely rests against your body, ready for the next repetition.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Kettlebell', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736364656Screenshot_99.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/8PmsnaHUJPU', 'Y', '2025-01-08 19:30:56', 'uploads/thumb/17363646561736364656screenshot_99.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1);
INSERT INTO `workout` (`id`, `routine_id`, `workout_title`, `workout_tipe`, `workout_desc`, `workout_type`, `equipments`, `rep`, `sets`, `worktime`, `image`, `video_type`, `url_type`, `video_path`, `status`, `update_on`, `workout_image_thumb`, `workout_level_id`, `musclegroup`, `min_calorie`, `max_calorie`, `week_no`, `day_no`) VALUES
(99, 5, 'Kettlebell Windmill', 'Always look at the weight when overhead.', '<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">1. Position the feet</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Turn your feet slightly away from the arm holding the kettlebell (around 45 degrees).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">2. Lock the kettlebell overhead</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Press the kettlebell into an overhead position, keeping the arm fully extended and the wrist locked.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">3. Bend the opposite knee</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slightly bend the knee on the opposite leg to help you stabilize and engage your core.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">4. Lower into the stretch</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Slowly lower your torso toward the floor, pushing your hips back and down while feeling a stretch along the inner thigh of the bent leg.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">5. Maintain arm alignment</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As you lower down, rotate your shoulder and arm outward to keep your kettlebell arm fully vertical throughout the movement.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">6. Reach for the ground</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Continue lowering your body as far as your mobility allows, aiming to bring your hand toward the floor or your ankle without compromising the vertical position of your overhead arm.</span></p>', '', 'Kettlebell', 5, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736369383Screenshot_100.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/ZENVpUgjHA8', 'Y', '2025-01-08 20:49:43', 'uploads/thumb/17363693831736369383screenshot_100.png', 4, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(100, 10, 'Kettlebell Snatch', 'Can be performed using a dumbbell', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin from the floor or standing, holding the kettlebell with one hand.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Explosive Motion</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: In one fluid motion, swing the kettlebell up, driving through your hips, and bring it overhead as quickly as possible.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Keep the Kettlebell Close</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: To maintain control and efficiency during the swing, keep the kettlebell close to your body.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Kettlebell', 8, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736490353Screenshot_101.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/MecShEmWEac', 'Y', '2025-01-10 06:25:53', 'uploads/thumb/17364903531736490353screenshot_101.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(101, 10, 'American Kettlebell Swing', 'Ensure the power comes from your hips, not your shoulders', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding the kettlebell with both hands </span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">in front of you</span><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hinge at the Hips</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Push your hips back, keeping the kettlebell close to your hips while maintaining a neutral back.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hip Thrust and Swing</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Explosively thrust your hips forward, swinging the kettlebell above your head quickly.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Don\'t Hold Overhead</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As the kettlebell swings overhead, let it rotate into an upside-down position at the top&mdash;avoid pausing or holding it there.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return to Start</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Control the descent, allow the kettlebell to swing back between your legs, and repeat the movement.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Kettlebell', 25, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736490961Screenshot_102.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/IfAbztBCEVU', 'Y', '2025-01-10 06:36:01', 'uploads/thumb/17364909611736490961screenshot_102.png', 3, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(102, 10, 'Dumbbell Clean', 'Focus on driving your elbows forward and up to catch the dumbbells in the front rack position smoothly.', '<ol style=\"color: #0e101a; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start in Standing Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing inward).</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set Up for the Deadlift</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Hinge at your hips and bend your knees slightly, lowering the dumbbells toward the floor. Keep your back neutral (flat) and your chest up.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Touch the dumbbell to the Floor</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: In a controlled motion, lower the dumbbells until one side of the dumbbell lightly touches the floor, maintaining good posture.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Explode Upward</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: In one swift motion, drive through your legs, extend your hips, and pull the dumbbells upward. Keep your elbows slightly bent as you lift.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Rotate the Elbows Under</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As the dumbbells rise, quickly rotate your elbows underneath them, bringing them to your shoulders in a \"front rack\" position (with the dumbbells resting on the front of your shoulders and palms facing upward).</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Hold the Front Rack Position</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Stand tall with a neutral spine once in the front rack, keeping your core engaged and elbows pointing forward.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: decimal;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Return to Start</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: To complete the movement, reverse the motion by lowering the dumbbells to the floor maintaining your neutral back position.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Kettlebell', 10, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736491407Screenshot_103.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/qFXvWbboBCE', 'Y', '2025-01-10 06:43:27', 'uploads/thumb/17364914071736491407screenshot_103.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(103, 10, 'Goblet squat', 'Can be performed using a dumbbell', '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Set Up the Kettlebell Hold</strong>: Hold it by the handle with both hands, positioning it like a bowl against your chest. Keep your elbows tucked in close to your body.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Engage Your Core</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Brace your core and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly pointed outward.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Lower Into the Squat</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Begin the movement by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering your body into a squat.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Keep Your Chest Up</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Maintain a proud chest and keep your back straight throughout the squat. Avoid rounding your back or leaning forward.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Track Your Knees</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Make sure your knees track over your toes, not caving inward, and your heels stay firmly planted on the floor.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Reach Full Depth</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Lower your body until your thighs parallel the floor (or deeper if your mobility allows), keeping your weight in your heels.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Return to Standing</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Push through your heels and rise back to the starting position, fully extending your hips and knees.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Kettlebell', 20, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736491781Screenshot_104.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/TWBwMhhu_po', 'Y', '2025-01-10 06:49:42', 'uploads/thumb/17364917811736491781screenshot_104.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(104, 10, 'Goblet Lunge', 'Can be performed using a dumbbell', '<ol style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; margin-top: 0cm;\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Set Up the Goblet Hold</strong>: Hold a dumbbell or kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body. This is the \"goblet\" position.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Step Into the Lunge</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Take a big step forward (or backward, depending on your preference) with one leg, lowering your body into the lunge.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Lower Your Hips</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: As you lunge, bend both knees to about 90 degrees. Your back knee should almost touch the floor, while your front knee should align over your ankle (not extend past your toes).</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Keep Your Back Straight</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Throughout the movement, maintain an upright torso, engaging your core to avoid leaning forward.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Return to Starting Position</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position, bringing your feet together.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: #0e101a;\"><strong>Repeat</strong><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">: Alternate legs or continue with the same leg, depending on your routine.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'Kettlebell', 12, 4, NULL, 'uploads/image/1736492120Screenshot_105.png', 'URL', 'server', 'https://youtu.be/zzV-Nd2ofpk', 'Y', '2025-01-10 06:55:20', 'uploads/thumb/17364921201736492120screenshot_105.png', 2, 'All Muscles Used', NULL, NULL, 1, 1);
